CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 16, 1960, pg.18 reads: "Receives Citation - during the recent annual dinner meeting sponsored by the religious education committee of Kay Boys Club, the Rev. George Daniel Little, left, pastor of Friendship Community U.P. Church, was one of several humanitarians cited for their unselfish support of the Kay Club. William B. Lillies, right, president of the Kay Club board, presents the award, while Councilman Paul F. Jones, left center, and Robert Dickey look on. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of George Daniel Little, left, pastor of Friendship Community U.P. Church, was cited for support of the Kay Boys' Club by William B. Lillies, right, while Paul F. Jones, left center, and Robert Dickey look on, standing in Kay Boys' Club
